00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:36.140
And the focus also on the
local history and culture.

00:30:36.140 --> 00:30:41.750 position:63%
Kindergarten through 5th grade students
in rural and small urban schools learned

00:30:41.750 --> 00:30:45.470
about the history and traditions
of their own home towns

00:30:45.470 --> 00:30:49.850
and about the wider Appalachian
culture as they explored their past

00:30:49.850 --> 00:30:52.000 position:56%
and present through multiple lenses.

00:30:56.040 --> 00:31:00.310 position:73%
First graders looked through the lens of homes.

00:31:00.310 --> 00:31:05.360 position:61%
As we were reminded yesterday during
Carol Highsmith's keynote presentation,

00:31:05.360 --> 00:31:10.820 position:72%
if you were lucky to -- lucky enough to sit in
on that -- it was a fantastic presentation --

00:31:10.820 --> 00:31:14.970 position:59%
