and understood through photographs.

00:31:20.470 --> 00:31:25.810 position:63%
First graders developed visual analysis
skills as well as their reading and math

00:31:25.810 --> 00:31:29.990
and fine motor skills in
their study of local homes.

00:31:29.990 --> 00:31:35.660 position:61%
Local photographs paired with digitized
images were analyzed for historic

00:31:35.660 --> 00:31:43.290 position:67%
and architectural detail and later compared
and contrasted with modern built homes.

00:31:43.290 --> 00:31:49.160 position:69%
Next students worked to create scaled
diagrams of their own houses and they worked

00:31:49.160 --> 00:31:52.930
with family members to measure
and draw important features.

00:31:52.930 --> 00:31:59.390 position:58%
As a final project, students created
model homes of their very own design.

00:31:59.390 --> 00:32:04.040 position:72%
Discussion throughout the unit helped students
think deeply about the change over time

00:32:04.040 --> 00:32:09.060
and local cultural and --
cultural practices and changes.

00:32:09.060 --> 00:32:10.840 position:58%
Working with parents and grandparents

00:32:10.840 --> 00:32:16.810 position:66%
and discussing the project helped families
make connections with historical items

00:32:16.810 --> 00:32:21.360 position:61%
and family heirlooms in brand new ways.

00:32:21.360 --> 00:32:26.400
Third graders at Cabell County
focused on the local school culture

00:32:26.400 --> 00:32:31.210
as their compared historic images
with modern day observations.

00:32:31.210 --> 00:32:36.160
They discussed daily activities and
compared classroom technologies.

00:32:36.160 --> 00:32:40.400 position:64%
They interviewed their family members
and considered how the school experiences

00:32:40.400 --> 00:32:47.900 position:72%
of their elders differed from their own
experiences and why these differences existed.

00:32:47.900 --> 00:32:52.060
One Cabell County school, Martha
Elementary, is featured here.

00:32:52.060 --> 00:32:56.140 position:63%
The image on the lower right shows the
old school house before it was destroyed

00:32:56.140 --> 00:32:57.490
by flooding.

00:32:57.490 --> 00:33:00.780 position:73%
