00:33:00.780 --> 00:33:05.560
to the original location, but
in a less flood prone area.

00:33:05.560 --> 00:33:11.100 position:56%
Martha Elementary stands testament
to the local community's resilience.

00:33:11.100 --> 00:33:15.870 position:58%
Geography paired with environmentally
factors, population changes,

00:33:15.870 --> 00:33:22.180 position:69%
and economic conditions all played key roles
in this study of the local school system.

00:33:22.180 --> 00:33:26.170
In the end, students even
got to make recommendations

00:33:26.170 --> 00:33:31.000 position:72%
that they thought would help improve their own
schools promoting civic competence and action.

00:33:37.130 --> 00:33:39.290
Cabell County schools saw the need

00:33:39.290 --> 00:33:44.620 position:72%
to move beyond the traditional textbook driven
curriculum and to move away from passive,

00:33:44.620 --> 00:33:49.370 position:63%
unengaging student learning environments
by incorporating primary sources

00:33:49.370 --> 00:33:53.320 position:70%
as an integral part of classroom instruction.

00:33:53.320 --> 00:33:58.670 position:58%
This TPS initiative provided ongoing
and embedded professional development

00:33:58.670 --> 00:34:05.000 position:72%
for Cabell County teachers focused on locating
and carefully selecting primary sources

00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:10.300 position:56%
from LOC.gov and other local
sources to promote inquiry learning.

00:34:10.300 --> 00:34:16.860 position:69%
As Michael and Ilene mentioned earlier, the
careful selection of primary sources for use

00:34:16.860 --> 00:34:21.400 position:69%
with young children is of utmost importance.

00:34:21.400 --> 00:34:26.860 position:66%
Miss Richardson's report on the results
